Design Decisions: 

1.Clean and Minimal Interface:
The interface was intentionally designed to be clean and uncluttered to support focus and ease of use.

# Decisions made:

- Avoid unnecessary elements or distractions
- Use whitespace to separate sections and content
- Use cards to group related information
- Keep screens simple and task-focused

# Why this matters:
A minimal interface improves usability and reduces cognitive load, especially for users who may already be stressed about hospital bills.

2. Clear Typography for Financial Data:
Typography was used as a tool to highlight important informations especially financial information.

# Decisions made:
- Larger font sizes for bill amounts and totals
- Medium font for section headings
- Smaller font for supporting text
- Consistent font hierarchy across all screens

# Why this matters:
Users can quickly identify critical financial information like:
- Total bill
- Amount owed
- Monthly payment
- Due dates
This reduces confusion and prevents payment mistakes.

3. Consistent Spacing and Layout:
A consistent spacing system was used across all screens to maintain visual balance and structure.

# Decisions made:
- Uniform padding and margins
- 8-point spacing system
- Grid-based layout for alignment
- Consistent card and component spacing

# Why this matters:
Consistency makes the interface predicatable. When users understand one screen, they can easily understand others

4. Strong Visual Hierarchy for Key Actions:
Primary actions were made visually prominent so users know what to do next.

# Decisions made:
- Primary buttons like “Split Bill” and “Confirm Payment” are bold and highly visible
- Secondary actions are less visually prominent
- Important information is placed at the top of screens
-  Actions are placed where users expect them (bottom or right side)

# Why this matters:
This guides users toward completing key tasks without confusion and improves task completion rate.

# Design Principles:
CareSplit design is built around four main principles, They are: 
                 
-- Simplicity - Clean UI, minimal screens, clear flow
-- Clarity - Clear financial breakdown and typography
-- Trust - Transparent payment information and structured layout
-- Efficiency - Fast payment flow and clear call-to-action buttons
These principles ensure that CareSplit delivers a user experience that is not only functional, but also intuitive and reliable.

# Design Process Summary
Defined the problem (medical bill splitting and payment difficulty)
Identified users (patients and hospital providers)
Created Personas, user flows for bill splitting and payment
Created Information Architecture to map out how caresplit will be built
Designed wireframes
Designed high-fidelity screens in Figma
Applied design system (colors, typography, spacing, components)
Designed both Patient and Provider dashboards
Focused on clarity of financial information and ease of payment
